<HEAD>&para; How vpon a tyme this Duke and duche&s;&s;e wal|ked allone &s;ore complaynynge the one to the other y^t they coude haue no chylde togyder</HEAD>
<P>VPon a tyme this duke &amp; duche&s;&s;e walked and the duke began to &s;hewe his mynde to his lady &s;aynge thus madame we be not fortuna|te in &s;o moche that we canne gete no chylderne and they that made y^e maryage betwene vs both they dyde grete &s;ynne for I beleue &amp; ye had ben gyuen to an other man ye &s;holde haue had chyldern and I al+&s;o yf I hadde an other ladye / this Lady vnder&s;to|de hy<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="MURP" EXTENT="1 letter"> &s;ayenge &s;he an&s;wered &s;oftly / &s;ayenge thus good lorde we mu&s;te thanke god of that whyche he &s;endeth vs &amp; take it pacyently of what &s;o euer it he.</P>
