<PB REF="5"> lyf &amp; &s;hall do as longe as the worlde &s;tondeth / wha~ this chylde was. &s;euen. yere olde or there aboute the duke his fader / &s;eynge and con&s;yderynge his wyc|ked condicions called hym and &s;ayde vnto hy~ thus my &s;one me thynke it nece&s;&s;ary and tyme / for me to gete you a wy&s;e &s;cole may&s;ter and put you to &s;cole / to lerne vertues and doctrine for ye be of age ynou|ghe and whan the duke had thus &s;ayde / he betoke his &s;one to a good di&s;cret and wy&s;e &s;cole may&s;ter to rule and teche hym al good condicions &amp; maners</P>
